OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1772103930
OL,3,CWarmer weather set to bring 'welcome
OL,4,Cexplosion' of spring colour, RHS says
OL,6,FThe charity said late-winter flowering
OL,7,Fbulbs and shrubs including crocus,
OL,8,Fsnowdrops, witch-hazels and hellebores
OL,9,Falready out in RHS gardens are being
OL,10,Fquickly joined by early daffodils,
OL,11,Fcamellias, cyclamen and hyacinths in
OL,12,Fthe mild conditions.
OL,14,FTim Upson, RHS director of gardens and
OL,15,Fhorticulture, said spring plants at
OL,16,Fthe charity's sites were coming into
OL,17,Fflower very quickly, and there was
OL,18,Flikely to be a "welcome explosion of
OL,19,Fcolour and new life over the next two
OL,20,Fweeks".
OL,26,@zD@POU|D@FO]
